product_image_analysis.prompt:
Analyze the product image and generate catalog metadata for a Christian art and photography marketplace.
Return only valid JSON with this exact shape: { "title": "short descriptive product title", "description": "one clear ecommerce product description paragraph, 80-180 words", "primary_keywords": ["most important visual/concept keywords"], "secondary_keywords": ["supporting subject, setting, style, season, emotion, and usage keywords"], "tertiary_keywords": ["additional related search terms"] }
Guidelines: - Base the result on visible image content only. Do not invent a Bible verse, artist name, SKU, denomination, or historical event unless visible in the image. - Keep the title natural and specific, not keyword-stuffed. - Use concise keyword phrases suitable for catalog search facets. - Prefer Christian art vocabulary when the image supports it, such as Jesus, Christ, cross, prayer, church, Bible, worship, resurrection, nativity, shepherd, disciples, angel, heaven, faith, grace, hope, love, Easter, Christmas. - Put the strongest 3-8 terms in primary_keywords, 5-12 in secondary_keywords, and 5-15 in tertiary_keywords. - Do not wrap JSON in markdown or code fences.
